.\" ManPage for `gsync'

.TH gsync 1 "14 November 2022" "1.0" "gsync man page"

.SH NAME
gsync \- All-in-One git command

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gsync [-v] [-u] [-h] [-m
.I message
.B ] [-t
.I tag-name
.B ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gsync
is a powerful command to use easily git! In just one line, you can add all your files, commit and push with tags if you want.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -v
enable verbose mode. Default verbose mode is off.
.TP
.B -u
add only the files updated. Default is all
.TP
.B -h
show help from the program and exit.
.TP
.B "-m message"
set the message for the commit. Default is "[autocommit]: Work in Progress".
.TP
.B "-t tag-name"
set the tag-name, and push following tags. Default tags are off.

.SH SEE ALSO
git(1)

.SH AUTHOR
Xavier <EAGLE> de Place
.I https://github.com/Xavier2p
